 border=0><td width='98' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma' size='2'>Character Level</td><td width='499' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma'size='2'>25 - 29</td></tr><tr><td width='98' align='left' bgcolor='#000000' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma' size='2'>Solo/Group</td><td width='499' align='left' bgcolor='#000000' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma'size='2'>Solo</td></tr><tr><td width='98' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma' size='2'>Zone</td><td width='499' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma'size='2'>Warslik Woods</td></tr><tr><td width='98' align='left' bgcolor='#000000' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma' size='2'>XP</td><td width='499' align='left' bgcolor='#000000' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma'size='2'>9</td></tr><tr><td width='98' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma' size='2'>Loot</td><td width='499' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma'size='2'>6</td></tr><tr><td width='98' align='left' bgcolor='#000000' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma' size='2'>Danger</td><td width='499' align='left' bgcolor='#000000' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma'size='2'>9</td></tr><tr><td width='98' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma' size='2'>Mob</td><td width='499' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma'size='2'>Forest Giants</td></tr><tr><td width='98' align='left' bgcolor='#000000' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma' size='2'>Mob Level</td><td width='499' align='left' bgcolor='#000000' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma'size='2'>22 - 25</td></tr><tr><td width='98' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma' size='2'>Location</td><td width='499' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma'size='2'>?</td></tr><tr><td width='98' align='left' bgcolor='#000000' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma' size='2'>Factions</td><td width='499' align='left' bgcolor='#000000' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma'size='2'>-TheKromdul</td></tr><tr><td width='98' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma' size='2'>Spells Used</td><td width='499' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma'size='2'>Heart Flutter, Engulfing Darkness, Heat Blood, Leach, Spirit Armor, Intensify Death, Drain Life spell</td></tr><tr><td width='98' align='left' bgcolor='#000000' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma' size='2'>Strategy</td><td width='499' align='left' bgcolor='#000000' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma'size='2'>Two words.  Forest Giants.<br><br>

Great XP from 26 to 29. Ive gone from 26-29 in about 12 hours of play.<br><br>

You can't Fear kite them as they are virtually immune at level 26, though it starts to stick better at 28.  But once darkness sticks and pet is on them, it is easy to regular kite them.  However, MAKE SURE DARKNESS STICKS.  These guys hit for up to 58 each time so running away is vital.<br><br>

Here is my strategy.  Park pet on the bridge opposite side of the fort from the OT zone.<br><br>

Buff both of you.  Cast Intensify.  Run into fort and pull a giant with Darkness.  Run back to pet.  While running if darkness has stuck, cast Heat Blood and if you have time, Heart Flutter.  If you don't get time then cast these after pet attacks.  Cast Leach (even if you don't need it, the extra damage helps).<br><br>

At this point, he will aggro on you and chase you.  Run back up the hill, check now and again to see if the pet has taunted him off you.  If pet taunts him off: recast darkness.  SoP or Lifetap, up to you, but you want him down fast as he will be creaming your pet.  This strategy has worked for me for three levels.  The FG's drop up to 3pp, rarely Black Pearls, and magic lore weapons worth about 18 to a vendor.<br><br>

Sit to med on the far side of the bridge, up the hill a little.  The only thing that will bother you is the occasional skellie or low level Gobbie which your pet will take out for you.<br><br>

Best of all, you get faction with Iksar and FV for every gobbie your pet kills and you can pick up a lot of bones from the skellies.  This has got to be the best spot for Necros at this level bar none.</td></tr><tr><td width='98' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma' size='2'>Author</td><td width='499' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma'size='2'><a href ='mailto:bleu@paradise.net.nz'>Ulaa Grimheart</td></tr><tr></table><br><br><table border='0' width=611><tr><td width='100%' colspan='2' bgcolor='#21456B'><p align='left' style='word-spacing: 0; margin: 0'><b><font color='#FFFFFF' size='2' face='Tahoma'>Additional Comments</font></b></td></tr><td width='17%'><font color='#FFFFFF' size='2' face='Tahoma'>Azhathoth</font></td><td width='83%'><font color='#FFFFFF' size='2' face='Tahoma'>I did 24-27 at the forest giants in a little over 12 hours total. You can invis to get past the 2 giants that guard the bridge at the entrance to the giant fort facing the Overthere zone, run up the hill to your right that is inside the fort wall, and make your camp. I did not have to kite the giants to kill them, and I very rarely got a bad pull where more than one giant came along. The few times that I did, it was easy to feign until they walked away.<br><br>

The method I used was to Intensify my pet, tell him to /guard the hill, run down into the fort and pull a giant with Darkness, run back up the hill, Leach, send pet, Flutter, wait a bit, Heat Blood (not necessary on the lower blues), and SoP/Siphon as needed to help the pet. More often than not I would end a fight with over half mana and 4 bubbles of health, with a pet at 1/3 to 1/2 health. The trick is to keep the giant on your pet for most of the fight, and only tank for your pet when necessary. If a giant sticks on you, feign or harmshield to let your pet get back up on its hate list.<br><br>

The difficulty of the giants from easiest to most difficult is: Sapling, Greenwood, Evergreen.<br><br>

Saplings hit for mid-hi 30s, Greenwoods from high 30s to 50, and the Evergreens for up to 56. All of them can double-attack, with the Evergreens doubling up quite often.<br><br>

There is also a plain "forest giant" that occasionally spawns in one of the huts in the center of the village. He conned the same as Greenwoods but hit for the same damage as the Saplings.<br><br>

Don't get in over your head, and keep feign memorized! Be careful pulling yellows since you can't kite them around, and they hit hard and fast. Of the few times I had to feign to save my life, it was due to a yellow-con Evergreen beating me to a pulp. However, I only died once during the 3 levels I spent here, and it was from going LD in the middle of a fight. Play it smart and you'll do fine.<br><br>

Loot here ranges from silver/copper on up to 3 plat. The giants loot a no-drop Evergreen Ringband every time, and occasionally drop Legchoppers and Giant Tree Flayers. The legchoppers sell for around 20 plat to the merchants back in the Overthere outpost. Don't give them to your pet, it slows him down WAY too much; same with the Tree Flayers.<br><br>

Also, these giants supposedly drop Forest Loops, which are an in-demand item for Druids and Rangers (they sell for up to 2k on Fennin), but I never saw one in the time I spent here.</font></td></tr></table></td></table></div>